# Testing

- Add tests for meaningful logic, especially routing, config, metrics, token/cost estimation, and fallback.
- Prefer integration tests for HTTP endpoints.
- Avoid tests that depend on real external provider APIs.
- Use mock providers or mock HTTP servers for provider behavior.
- Test failure cases, not just happy paths.
- Keep test data explicit and readable.
- Ensure examples remain valid JSON.
- Required coverage areas include config parsing, health, readiness, chat success, invalid chat requests, mock failure, fallback behavior, all providers failed, metrics aggregation, cost estimation, and request ID propagation.
